    "## Why Neural Networks Stalled Again (1990s)\n",
    "\n",
    "Despite backpropagation's power, networks struggled through the 1990s due to limited data, insufficient compute, unstable optimization, and competing methods (SVMs). This led to the **second AI Winter**.\n",
    "\n",
    "## AlexNet and the Deep Learning Breakthrough (2012)\n",
    "\n",
    "@krizhevsky2012imagenet presented **AlexNet**, winning ImageNet with ~16% top-5 error (vs ~26% previously).\n",
    "Key innovations: ReLU activations, dropout regularization, GPU training.\n",
    "Lesson: deep networks scale with **data + compute**.\n",
    "\n",
    "## The Transformer Era (2017)\n",
    "\n",
    "The transformer @vaswani2017attention replaced recurrence with **self-attention**, enabling parallelization and long-range dependencies:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\text{Attention}(Q, K, V) = \\text{softmax}\\!\\left(\\frac{QK^\\top}{\\sqrt{d_k}}\\right)V\n",
    "$$ {#eq-004-attention}\n",
    "\n",
    "Transformers proved extraordinarily scalable, launching the era of Large Language Models.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Natural Language Processing: From Rules to Neural Networks\n",
    "\n",
    "## The Challenge of Text\n",
    "\n",
    "Text must be transformed into **numbers** before a neural network can process it.\n",
    "Early NLP developed a sequence of representations, each more powerful than the last.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Tokenization\n",
    "\n",
    "**Tokenization** splits raw text into discrete units called *tokens*."
