    "## N-Grams\n",
    "\n",
    "**N-grams** capture local context by treating sequences of $n$ consecutive words as features:\n",
    "\n",
    "| N-gram Type | Example from \"strong revenue growth\" |\n",
    "|-------------|--------------------------------------|\n",
    "| Unigram (n=1) | \"strong\", \"revenue\", \"growth\" |\n",
    "| Bigram (n=2) | \"strong revenue\", \"revenue growth\" |\n",
    "| Trigram (n=3) | \"strong revenue growth\" |\n",
    "\n",
    "N-grams allow BoW models to capture phrases like *\"not good\"* vs *\"good\"* — critical for sentiment analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Classification with Neural Networks\n",
    "\n",
    "## Text Classification\n",
    "\n",
    "**Text classification** assigns a label to a piece of text:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Task | Input | Output |\n",
    "|------|-------|--------|\n",
    "| Spam detection | Email | Spam / Not Spam |\n",
    "| Sentiment analysis | Review | Positive / Negative / Neutral |\n",
    "| Topic labeling | Article | Sports / Finance / Tech |\n",
    "| Intent detection | Query | Order / Refund / Info |\n",
    "\n",
    "## Sentiment Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Given: *\"The product quality was exceptional, and delivery was fast.\"* → **Positive**\n",
    "\n",
    "Given: *\"The item broke after one use. Complete waste of money.\"* → **Negative**\n",
    "\n",
    "Early approaches used hand-crafted sentiment lexicons.\n",
    "The neural approach: learn the mapping text → label **end-to-end** from labeled examples.\n",
    "\n",
    "## MLP for Text Classification\n",
    "\n",
    "Standard pipeline:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\text{Raw Text} \\xrightarrow{\\text{tokenize}} \\text{Tokens} \\xrightarrow{\\text{vectorize}} \\mathbf{x} \\xrightarrow{\\text{MLP}} \\hat{y}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "### PyTorch Implementation"
   ]
