    "## MLP Architecture Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "| Layer | Role |\n",
    "|-------|------|\n",
    "| **Input** | TF-IDF vector of dimension $|V|$ |\n",
    "| **Hidden** | Learn non-linear feature combinations |\n",
    "| **Output** | One logit per class; softmax -> probabilities |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key limitation**: TF-IDF + MLP ignores word order, motivating RNNs, CNNs for text, and ultimately Transformers.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# How Generative Models Work\n",
    "\n",
    "## Representing Data as Distributions\n",
    "\n",
    "Traditional classification estimates $P(y \\mid \\mathbf{x})$.\n",
    "Generative models estimate $P(\\mathbf{x})$ or $P(\\mathbf{x}, y)$, allowing them to **generate** new examples.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Next-Token Prediction\n",
    "\n",
    "At its core, a generative language model predicts:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "P(w_t \\mid w_1, w_2, \\ldots, w_{t-1})\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Stacking this prediction across billions of parameters and trillions of training tokens produces systems capable of complex reasoning, code synthesis, summarization, and creative writing.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Limitations of Generative AI\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Hallucinations**: Models fabricate details when lacking reliable context\n",
    "- **Bias**: Training data biases appear in model outputs\n",
    "- **No true understanding**: Statistical pattern manipulation, not comprehension\n",
    "- **Explainability**: Reasoning behind outputs is difficult to audit\n",
    "- **Resource demands**: Substantial compute required for training and deployment\n",
    "\n",
    "Understanding these limitations — grounded in the history of how these systems were built — is essential for responsible deployment in business and analytics contexts.\n",
